    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-06T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="11"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.5151/145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sevier</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-06T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 6, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Your telegram No. 18. The question has been discussed with the
                    representatives of Baldwin and an interview with the Foreign Office has been
                    arranged for tomorrow. In the meantime the Baldwin representative[s] believe it
                    will be helpful for the Department to talk to the Chilean Ambassador who was
                    formerly Director General of Railways and who might be disposed to cable his
                    Government recommending <pb facs="0076" n="10" xml:id="pg_10"/> the continued
                    use of Baldwin equipment. The contract will probably be awarded shortly after
                    the return of the Minister of Finance from leave on Thursday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sevier</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
